commText: Welcome back for the run chase.. The CSK players are gathered in a huddle, Pathirana joins them. He's the impact sub. A slip in place and here we go!

Most runs in the middle overs (7-16) in IPL 2024 220 - Riyan Parag (SR: 152.77) 191 - Shivam Dube (SR: 166.08) 159 - Sai Sudharsan (SR: 134.74) 153 - Virat Kohli (SR: 145.71) 153 - Sanju Samson (SR: 159.37) CSK innings progression Overs 1-4: 24/1 (RR: 6) Overs 5-9: 41/1 (RR: 8.2) Overs 10-15: 84/0 (RR: 14) Overs 16-19: 31/1 (RR: 7.75) Last over: 26/1 Bumrah in death overs (17-20) in IPL 2024 Overs: 8 Runs conceded: 59 Wickets: 6 Avg: 9.83 ER: 7.37 MI bowling today Bumrah and Nabi: 0/46 from 7 overs (ER: 6.57) Others: 4/157 from 13 overs (ER: 12.07) Dhoni batting in the 20th over in the IPL Runs: 756 Balls: 309 SR: 244.66 4s/6s: 51/64 This season: 41 off 12, two fours, five sixes (SR: 341.66) Dhoni vs Hardik in the IPL Before today: 22 off 27, one dismissal, (SR: 81.48) Today: 20 off 4 (SR: 500)

Gerald Coetzee: Around about par (total). The pitch gets better as the night gets on because of dew. That's what happened in the last game. Very beneficial (to be alongside Bumrah). He (Bumrah) is probably the best in the world in this format, so learn from him. I'm loving it (the IPL). Great conditions here for cricket and you need to be at your best.

21:23 Local Time, 15:53 GMT, 21:23 IST: A pretty stiff total posted by Chennai Super Kings but Mumbai Indians have chased down similar targets at the Wankhede before. Only a few days ago they chased down 195-plus against Royal Challengers Bangalore. Coming back to this game, the ploy to move Rahane up the order didn't work for CSK as Coetzee got his wicket within the powerplay. Ravindra too couldn't continue for long as he was dismissed by Shreyas Gopal in the 8th over. Just when MI had things under control, Dube and Gaikwad joined hands and had a fantastic partnership for the third wicket. Both the batters played some exquisite shots in their partnership and also notched up their fifties in the process. Shreyas Gopal bowled the only over due to Dube's threat, however, Shepherd was at the receiving end of some pyrotechnics instead. Bumrah bowled a couple of wily overs towards the end to restrict Mitchell, but Dhoni walked out to bat and hit a hat-trick of sixes in the final over of the innings. That was an icing on the cake. Back in 10 minutes for the second essay...

Hardik Pandya to Dhoni, 2 runs, Dhoni's cameo powers CSK to a daunting total of 206/4! Short and slow on off, Dhoni swings across the line, gets an inside edge past Kishan down the leg-side. A couple of runs taken to end the 20th over, 26 runs from it..

Hardik Pandya to Dhoni, SIX, hat-trick of sixes as 200 comes up! A full toss on the pads and Dhoni has flicked this over deep square leg. MI's present captain running out of ideas against CSK's former skipper. An absolute fest for Dhoni fans at the Wankhede

Hardik Pandya to Dhoni, SIX, two in two! Insane. Right into the slot, Dhoni stays put and clubs it over wide long-on for back-to-back sixes. Striking at a rate of 600. Enough content for social media to go berserk for the next few weeks
Hardik Pandya to Dhoni, SIX, and he starts off with a maximum! The crowd erupts. Slower delivery around off, Dhoni stands tall and smokes it over long-off for a six
MS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Out walks Dhoni with 4 balls to go..

Hardik Pandya to Mitchell, out Caught by Nabi!! Hardik Pandya gets Mitchell, probably a blessing in disguise as Mitchell was struggling out there. A full toss by Hardik Pandya and Mitchell lofts it straight to Nabi at long-on. A regulation catch taken.. Mitchell c Nabi b Hardik Pandya 17(14) [4s-1]
Hardik Pandya to Mitchell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Hardik Pandya to Mitchell, wide, full and wide outside off, misses the tramline again. The wide called has been challenged again by MI. Mitchell had shuffled a touch, but the ball was still out of his reach

Hardik Pandya to Mitchell, FOUR, Mitchell finally connects one. On a length around off and Mitchell thumps it over the bowler's head, just manages to beat the fielder who was charging to his left from long-on
Hardik Pandya to Mitchell, wide, goes wide outside off and it just misses the tramline, the wide decision stays..
Hardik Pandya [2.0-0-17-1] is back into the attack
A wide called by the umpire and MI have gone up for a review, challenging the onfield decision..
Bumrah to Mitchell, 1 run, quality over by Bumrah.. Ends it with another excellent yorker as Mitchell can only squeeze it past the bowler
Bumrah to Shivam Dube, 1 run, 144.3kph, quick into the blockhole, all Shivam Dube can do is squeeze it to long-on
Bumrah to Mitchell, 1 run, sticks to his yorker, Mitchell can't get underneath, just a single at long-on
"We want Dhoni," are the chants from the Wankhede crowd..
Bumrah to Mitchell, 2 runs, low full toss on off, Mitchell scoops this over the keeper and takes a couple of runs, stopped by the fielder sprinting across in the deep
Bumrah to Shivam Dube, 1 run, yorker length ball on middle, Shivam Dube digs it towards mid-on for a single
Bumrah to Mitchell, 1 run, squeezed along the carpet to long-off for a single
Gerald Coetzee to Shivam Dube, FOUR, boundary to end the over. Short and quick on leg, Shivam Dube goes for a pull, gets a top edge that flies over the keeper down the leg-side
Gerald Coetzee to Shivam Dube, no run, short and slow on leg, Shivam Dube looks to pull it away, it comes off the thigh pad and lobs next to the pitch
Can see MSD wearing his helmet and waiting in the dressing room.. Looks like he is in the mood to bat tonight..
Gerald Coetzee to Mitchell, 1 run, into the blockhole, Mitchell squeezes it to deep mid-on for one
Gerald Coetzee to Mitchell, 2 runs, sloppy fielding. Mitchell had heaved this towards long-on and Kishan couldn't gather the throw from Nabi, resulting in an overthrow
Gerald Coetzee to Shivam Dube, leg byes, 1 run, fired on leg, off the pads towards square leg as they take a leg bye
Gerald Coetzee to Shivam Dube, FOUR, full toss on middle and leg, Shivam Dube flicks it away to the deep square leg fence. Not all about power, he can't toy with the field too
Gerald Coetzee [3.0-0-24-1] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Shivam Dube, 1 run, 10 runs from the over. Bumrah bowls a low full toss on off as Shivam Dube squeezes it to long-off for a single

Bumrah to Shivam Dube, FOUR, finally connects one. A full toss outside off and Shivam Dube drills it through cover as the ball races away to the fence at the rate of knots. Much needed for CSK as the boundaries have dried up
Bumrah to Mitchell, 1 run, sticks to his yorker, Mitchell jams it out towards mid-on for a single
Bumrah to Mitchell, 2 runs, another ball right into the blockhole, Mitchell digs it out towards deep mid-on and takes two runs, good running between the wickets
Bumrah to Shivam Dube, 1 run, yorker length ball on middle and leg, Shivam Dube squeezes it to long-on for a single
Bumrah to Mitchell, 1 run, slower length ball outside off, Mitchell punches it through the off-side for a single
Jasprit Bumrah [2.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Hardik Pandya to Shivam Dube, no run, banged in short by Hardik Pandya, Shivam Dube goes for a pull, doesn't middle it as the ball lands in front of short fine leg
Hardik Pandya to Mitchell, 1 run, short of a length around middle and leg, heaved through mid-wicket by Mitchell along the carpet
Hardik Pandya to Mitchell, no run, on a length around off, keeps a tad low as Mitchell knocks it back to Hardik Pandya
Hardik Pandya to Mitchell, no run, back of a length around off, Mitchell knocks it down the pitch
Daryl Mitchell, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Strategic timeout! The platform has been laid for the power hitters from CSK to come in and make the most of the end overs. However, they got two overs from Bumrah to deal with. Will they reach the 200-run mark or will Bumrah stop them from getting there? We shall find out soon..

Hardik Pandya to Gaikwad, out Caught by Nabi!! Skipper Pandya strikes. Gives the much needed breakthrough. Goes full and slightly slow outside off, Gaikwad looks to take him on. Goes for the aerial route, but doesn't middle it. Nabi from long-on charges in and completes a fine running catch. Gaikwad walks back after playing his best knock of this season. Slowly but surely getting back into his groove. Gaikwad c Nabi b Hardik Pandya 69(40) [4s-5 6s-5]
Hardik Pandya to Gaikwad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Hardik Pandya to Shivam Dube, 1 run, fifty for Shivam Dube! On a length around off, Shivam Dube slashes it over cover-point to get to his fifty. Raises his bat to acknowledge the crowd. Has been the most consistent batter for CSK this season
Hardik Pandya [1.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack

11-15 Over Summary: >> Rohit puts down a catch of Gaikwad at deep mid-wicket >> Ruturaj scores two quick sixes after that, gets to 50 off 33 balls >> Dube sizes up Shepherd, hits him for two sixes and a four >> Gaikwad plunders a six and a four off Madhwal next over >> 79 runs scored in these five overs
Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, FOUR, 17 runs from the over! Another juicy delivery and Gaikwad makes room to carve it through point. Both the batters have some fun out in the middle. 200 on the cards

Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, SIX, exciting stuff! Runs coming thick and fast from both the ends. Was a full toss outside off, Gaikwad advances down the wicket and slices it over Shepherd at deep point. A flat six that was!

Akash Madhwal to Shivam Dube, 1 run, that was off the cue end, but doesn't carry to the fielder. Was a low full toss around off and Shivam Dube lofted it to long-on, miscued it, but the fielder charging in from the deep can't get anywhere close

Akash Madhwal to Shivam Dube, FOUR, just eludes the fielder at cover. Shivam Dube had smashed it uppishly and the fielder at cover dives to his right, fails to get his hand to it though. Was Rohit Sharma who couldn't get there
Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, 1 run, yorker length ball on off, Gaikwad squeezes it into the off-side for one
Fastest to 2,000 IPL runs (by innings taken) 48 - Chris Gayle 52 - Shaun Marsh 57 - Ruturaj Gaikwad 60 - KL Rahul 63 - Sachin Tendulkar
Akash Madhwal to Shivam Dube, 1 run, nails the wide yorker outside off, Shivam Dube opens the bat face, squeezing it through backward point for a single
Akash Madhwal [2.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
Last 24 balls - 52 runs
Shepherd to Gaikwad, FOUR, Shepherd goes for 22 runs in the over. A low full toss outside off and Gaikwad opens the bat face to carve this through backward point for a rollicking boundary

Shepherd to Shivam Dube, leg byes, 1 run, short of a length from round the wicket, cramped for room as the angle was round the wicket. Shivam Dube gets hit on the thigh pad as the ball rolls into the off-side

Shepherd to Shivam Dube, FOUR, 6,6,4 as the crowd is absolutely loving it. Shepherd goes short and Shivam Dube pulls it powerfully through mid-wicket, manages to beat the fielder's dive in the deep. Shepherd running out of ideas, that expression on his face says it all

Shepherd to Shivam Dube, SIX, this one's enornous! Shepherd getting a taste of his own medicine. He did something similar to Nortje a few days back at the same venue. At the receiving end tonight. Goes full and Shivam Dube launches it over long-on for half-a-dozen

Shepherd to Shivam Dube, SIX, Shivam Dube taking down the medium pacers. Short of a length on leg, Shivam Dube picks it up nicely and clears deep backward square leg, the fielder near the boundary was a mere spectator
Shepherd to Gaikwad, 1 run, pitched up by the bowler on off, Gaikwad chips it to long-off for a single
Romario Shepherd [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack

Gerald Coetzee to Shivam Dube, no run, oh was that a dropped chance? Short of a length delivery angling in, Dube looks to pull, cramped for room, under edge maybe but need replays. Ishan spilled it diving low to the right
Gerald Coetzee to Gaikwad, 1 run, backed away to go big on the off-side, Rutu drives and picks out mid-off as Coetzee followed him to give no room

Gerald Coetzee to Gaikwad, SIX, brilliant shot to raise his fifty! This guy loves pace on the ball and Gerald Coetzee offered slot too. Rutu with mid-off up just lofted it easily over long-off for a maximum

Gerald Coetzee to Shivam Dube, leg byes, 1 run, big shout for LBW from Gerald Coetzee, but Ishan isn't keen. It looked close but they weren't keen on the review. Length delivery angling in, Dube into a complete tangle on the flick, need a replay to see what ball-tracker had to say. Was it missing leg?
Gerald Coetzee to Shivam Dube, no run, lovely yorker, Dube only manages to toe-end it
Gerald Coetzee to Shivam Dube, no run, yorker, gets it decently right as a low full toss, Dube pushes it to cover
Gerald Coetzee [2.0-0-17-1] is back into the attack
What do MI do? Dube has struggled against Bumrah. But they have only two more overs off him. Do they risk an over now? Because if Dube carries on he could take this away towards him

Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, SIX, there's the one bad ball of the over that Rutu and CSK pounce on! Full and in the slot, Rutu goes aerial over long-on for an easy maximum to raise CSK's 100. Didn't get the middle of the bat but cleared the rope. Was a very good over until the final ball
Akash Madhwal to Shivam Dube, 1 run, short of length delivery on the leg stump, Dube flicks to deep mid-wicket

Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, 1 run, in the airrrr and put down! Tough chance though. Short of a length delivery, Gaikwad slogs it flat to deep mid-wicket. Rohit runs to the right and dives, did really well to get both hands to the ball despite it the ball dying on him but it didn't stick and the trousers come off too!
Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, no run, and again! Lovely off-side yorker, Rutu tries to squeeze it past point but misses it completely
Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, no run, yorker just outside off stump, Rutu digs it out. Well bowled and it did tail back in a tad
Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, 2 runs, drags the slog wide of mid-wicket but Romario does well to dive and save two at the fence
Akash Madhwal [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Shepherd to Shivam Dube, FOUR, poor ball! Point and third man in and he bowls short and wide to release pressure. Dube stands tall and happily accepts the gift to cut it over the infield for four
Shepherd to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, short of length delivery, Dube slaps it to past extra-cover

Shepherd to Gaikwad, 1 run, oh he's missed out on an easy boundary! Slow and down leg, would have been a wide, but Rutu thought he could help it away to the fine leg fence but he picks out short fine leg. Fumble still allowss a run. Tilak ensured he cut the angle off to the right from deep backward square leg to keep this to one
Shepherd to Shivam Dube, 1 run, another big swing from Dube, mistimes the slog to long-on off the back foot
Shepherd to Shivam Dube, no run, beaten! Dube has ensured CSK have got life back into the innings, so he's in the mood for more big hits. Has a wild slog and misses as Shepherd takes pace off

Shepherd to Shivam Dube, FOUR, in the airrrr and beats Hardik's full length dive at mid-off. Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Dube slaps it hard off the back foot, didn't middle it as well as he would have liked but he managed to escape mid-off
Romario Shepherd, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

6-10 Over Summary: >> Madhwal concedes 10 off his first over >> Nabi bowls another quiet over >> Ravindra out caught behind to a Shreyas Gopal googly >> Hardik Pandya bowls the 10th over, gets hit for 3 boundaries by Dube

Hardik Pandya to Gaikwad, 2 runs, oh brilliant punch-drive through cover and a really good diving save at the fence to save two. Fullish delivery outside off stump, Rutu leans forward and places it past extra-cover. 15 off that over and CSK have 80 on the board at the halfway stage
Hardik Pandya to Shivam Dube, 1 run, short of length delivery on the stumps, Dube knocks it to long-on

Hardik Pandya to Shivam Dube, FOUR, oh he's lost the line there! Tried the slower short delivery but it's well down leg-side, Dube easily helps it on its way to the fine leg fence. Pressure releasing over this from Hardik
Hardik Pandya to Shivam Dube, FOUR, neat off-drive! Fullish delivery outside off stump, Dube leans forward and drives wide of mid-off and it's racing away for four
Hardik Pandya to Shivam Dube, no run, blocked
Crowd still booing Hardik and a section of the crowd picks up "Hardik, Hardik" chants. The other section responds with boos again

Hardik Pandya to Shivam Dube, FOUR, if you are a pacer, you run in bowl short at Dube. That's the norm these days. But this wasn't really short, Dube rocked and played a nice swivel pull behind square for four
Hardik Pandya, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Seems like pace off is the way to go on this pitch and 180 could be a really good score with the anti-dew agent does its bit
Bumrah to Gaikwad, 2 runs, goes for the killer yorker but bowls another low full toss, Rutu takes his foot out and glances it to fine leg. Oh fumble allwos them a second run
Bumrah to Gaikwad, no run, slower delivery, Rutu waits and punches nicely but picks out backward point
Bumrah to Gaikwad, wide, short for the bumper, Rutu lets it go and gets a wide
Bumrah to Shivam Dube, 1 run, short of length delivery on the leg stump, Dube works it through backward square leg
Bumrah to Shivam Dube, no run, full toss as he doesn't get the yorker right, Dube drives to cover and sets off on a halfstop, Rutu sends him back
Bumrah to Shivam Dube, no run, pace off into the wicket, Dube defends off the back foot
Bumrah to Shivam Dube, no run, short of length delivery just outside off stump, Dube defends off the back foot
Jasprit Bumrah [1.0-0-6-0] is back into the attack
Will MI bowl spin at both ends to Dube? Why will they? Here's the matchup battle to Dube. Bumrah!
Rachin Ravindra vs spin in IPL 2024 Runs: 27 Balls: 16 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 9 SR: 168.75
Shreyas Gopal to Shivam Dube, 1 run, turning back in, Dube works it to mid-wicket
Shivam Dube, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Shreyas Gopal to Ravindra, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! Top call from Ishan Kishan! He was confident with the appeal and review. Shreyas Gopal surprised to see there was edge on the replay. Googly short and angling away, Ravindra goes back to cut, gets the toe-end of the bat and it's a good take by Ishan Kishan. MI get their second and pressure on CSK now. Ravindra c Ishan Kishan b Shreyas Gopal 21(16) [4s-2 6s-1]
Shreyas Gopal to Ravindra, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Caught behind review from MI. Nothing from the bowler. Ishan was so confident and pointed to his ears that he heard something and Hardik reviews without wasting time. Yes, bottom edge!
Shreyas Gopal to Ravindra, SIX, and Rachin manages to tee off! Googly expectedly wide of off stump, Rachin was ready for it and smashed it over long-on
Shreyas Gopal to Gaikwad, 1 run, googly on the stumps, Rutu goes back and guides it past point
Shreyas Gopal to Gaikwad, no run, flighted delivery on the off stump, Rutu defends off the front foot
This ain't the flattest of pitches for sure
Shreyas Gopal to Ravindra, 1 run, oh look at that roller from a shortish length! Ravindra was on the back foot but managed to slap it to long-off
Shreyas Gopal, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Brilliant over from Nabi - just four off it
Nabi to Ravindra, 1 run, goes back and flicks this flatter delivery to long-on
Nabi to Gaikwad, 1 run, fullish and turning back in, Gaikwad leans forward and drives to long-on
Nabi to Ravindra, 1 run, flatter delivery outside off stump, Ravindra pushes it to long-off
Nabi to Gaikwad, 1 run, worked away to mid-wicket
Crowd raise their voices as they show Dhoni on the screen and the chants of "Dhoni, Dhoni" begin
Nabi to Gaikwad, no run, lovely ball! Rushed Rutu on the glance with a flatter delivery, ball rolls behind square
Nabi to Gaikwad, no run, full and outside off stump, Gaikwad leans forward and drives to cover
Mohammad Nabi [2.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack

Early timeout! Very interesting to see MI take the timeout this early despite a pretty decent start from their bowlers. Rutu has ensured this PP wasn't bad for CSK while Rachin is still not middling them neat. Maybe they want to break Rutu's rhythm
Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, 1 run, moves across and softly dabs it to point for an easy single
Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, no run, tries to place this guide in the gap but picked out backward point. Middled that nicely again

Akash Madhwal to Gaikwad, FOUR, this is very good batting from Rutu! He's moving around in the crease according to the field and then placing the ball in gaps. Fine leg in, so he moves across and glances this short of length delivery behind square to collect four
Akash Madhwal to Ravindra, 1 run, this time he's cut this to deep backward point

Akash Madhwal to Ravindra, FOUR, oh dear! Should have been a dot ball but Shreyas Gopal has let this go right through him! Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Ravindra cuts straight to backward point and gets four instead

Akash Madhwal to Ravindra, no run, excellent yorker to start with from Akash Madhwal. Rachin digs it out to the on-side and looks for a run, Rutu not keen. Direct-hit at the striker's end but Rachin was home in time
Runout checkbut Rachin is home
Akash Madhwal, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

1-5 Over Summary: >> Rahane opens the batting for CSK >> The move flops as Rahane is out second over against Coetzee >> Nabi slips two quiet powerplay overs, concedes 15 >> Gaikwad takes down Coetzee, scores 14 runs off an over
Gerald Coetzee to Gaikwad, no run, now moves off-side and the bowler tries to push it slightly outside off stump, Rutu defends towards point
Gerald Coetzee to Gaikwad, no run, solid in defence to this fullish delivery targetting the stumps

Gerald Coetzee to Gaikwad, FOUR, but this is a friendly full toss to which no captain can set a field to. Rutu gets inside the line and clips it over mid-wicket for an easy boundary. CSK will feel better with runs coming in this over after a great start from MI
Hardik has a word with Coetzee and they have asked long leg to come in
Gerald Coetzee to Gaikwad, no run, now Rutu steps out and slogs, hits this length delivery pretty well but picks out mid-wicket

Gerald Coetzee to Gaikwad, SIX, now nails the upper cut! This is why he was backing away first ball. He knows Gerald Coetzee offers pace and bowls into the wicket, so he goes off-side to free his arms and slices it for a maximum

Gerald Coetzee to Gaikwad, FOUR, unlucky for the bowler! He did the right thing of following the batter as he backed away. Did rush the batter with a pact short of length delivery, Rutu just trying to fend and got lucky with a thick inside edge that escaped for four
Gerald Coetzee [1.0-0-3-1] is back into the attack

Bumrah to Ravindra, FOUR, flicked away past the diving square leg fielder and it's four. That will make him feel better. Good length delivery angling into the pads, Ravindra flicks and sends it to the boundary

Bumrah to Ravindra, no run, beaten! Rachin clearly struggling against Boom! The genuine outswinger now, Rachin on the charge looking for a drive, gets beaten on the outside edge. Smart of Bumrah to drop it into the wicket knowing the batter is expecting another full ball
Bumrah to Ravindra, no run, tries the toe-crusher again but bowls a low full toss, Ravindra mistimes the flick to the on-side
Bumrah to Ravindra, no run, short of length delivery, Ravindra punches it to short cover

Bumrah to Ravindra, wide, goes for the big inswinging full delivery from round the wicket, but fires down leg! Ravindra misses the glance. Bumrah has a soft check for caught behind but doesn't get support from his teammates
Bumrah to Gaikwad, 1 run, now hangs back and steer this short of length delivery down to third man
Bumrah to Gaikwad, no run, straightaway steps out to Bumrah and shortens the length. Rutu defends this short of length delivery to the on-side
Jasprit Bumrah, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Nabi to Ravindra, no run, oh Rachin missed out on a boundary there! Short and wide, he went back and slapped it really well, picked out the man at cover though
Nabi to Gaikwad, 1 run, bit of an uppish sweep, Rutu sends it to deep backward square leg

Stat: Gaikwad in his only previous outing at No.3 in T20s: 52(37) vs Baroda, Rajkot, SMAT 2017/18 \n - This is just the sixth instance of Gaikwad not opening the batting in his T20 career, third in the IPL. He registered a golden duck from No.5 on his IPL debut against RR followed by 5(10) in the very next game from No.4 against DC in 2020.
Nabi to Gaikwad, SIX, overpitched and Rutu goes aerial over long-on. He's gone down one knee to get under the ball and powered it over the fence. In the slot and he didn't miss out
Nabi to Ravindra, 1 run, round the wicket with a slip in place. Ravindra stays back and flicks to deep mid-wicket
Nabi to Gaikwad, 1 run, bit of grip! Turning down leg, Rutu works it to mid-wicket
Nabi to Gaikwad, no run, oh goes for the slog-sweep and misses. Gets hit on the right forearm, soft check for LBW. No interest from the ump or the home team for DRS
Gerald Coetzee to Gaikwad, 1 run, fullish delivery outside off stump, Gaikwad dabs to third man and he's away
Gerald Coetzee to Gaikwad, no run, short of length delivery just outside off stump, Gaikwad defends
Ruturaj Gaikwad, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Gerald Coetzee to Rahane, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! And there's the early wicket. The move to send Jinks up the order doesn't work. Short of a length delivery on the off stump, this one kicks up a bit, Rahane looks to pull on the rise, ball hits him high on the bat and it's total mishit for a dolly at mid-on. MI are off the mark early. Rahane c Hardik Pandya b Gerald Coetzee 5(8) [4s-1]
Gerald Coetzee to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Gerald Coetzee to Rahane, no run, oh inside edge onto pad! Gentle niblble away but lack of bounce doing the trick for Gerald Coetzee. Was slot, usually Rahane puts those away but seems like it didn't bounce that much
Gerald Coetzee to Rahane, no run, fullish delivery just outside off stump, Rahane defends
Gerald Coetzee to Ravindra, 1 run, fullish delivery on the stumps, Ravindra works it to mid-wicket
Gerald Coetzee to Ravindra, wide, tries the hide the ball wide of off straightaway and fires a wide
Gerald Coetzee, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
So CSK throwing in an early surprise by sending Jinks to open

Stat: The team winning the toss has won each of the last nine matches between MI and CSK, a sequence that started with MI's 1-run win in the 2019 final in Hyderabad. Seven of the last eight matches between these two sides - including each of the last four - have been won by the chasing side, featuring two last-ball finishes.
Nabi to Rahane, no run, full and straight on off, Rahane drives it to mid-off

Nabi to Rahane, FOUR, first boundary of the match! A flatter delivery by Nabi, Rahane goes for a sweep and gets a top edge that flies over backward square leg. Was in the air for a long time, but eludes the fielders chasing it
Nabi to Rahane, no run, fraction short on off, Rahane rocks back and cuts it to point
Nabi to Ravindra, 1 run, that kept low as Ravindra works it through mid-wicket for a single
Chants of 'CSK CSK' all across the Wankhede..
Nabi to Rahane, 1 run, flatter delivery on middle and leg, Rahane clips it through mid-wicket for a single
Nabi to Rahane, no run, tossed up delivery on off, driven to cover by Rahane
Rahane and Ravindra are at the crease. Rahane is on strike. Nabi will open the attack
